data.description: Charming two-story on a premium lot with a pond out front and woods to the back offering privacy galore. This 3 bedroom, 2.5 bath home in the McKewn neighborhood is move-in ready with many upgrades, new interior and exterior lighting, new interior paint, new board and batten accent wall in the living room, new privacy fence, renovated powder room, extended back patio, upgraded landscaping with new walkway lighting, and new solar panels. An inviting open floor plan downstairs with Luxury Vinyl Plank (LVP) flooring, living room/dining combo, large island, white cabinets, granite counters, stainless appliances, pantry, foyer and a powder room. Sliding doors from dining area to patio, large fenced back yard and a two car garage. Upstairs you will find the primary ensuite with walk-in closet,closet, dual vanity, and a large shower. Two additional bedrooms, the other full sized bath with tub/shower combo, and the laundry room. The solar panels consist of 10 LG panels and have drastically decreased the owner's power and gas bills. Not only do they decrease energy costs, help the environment but according to appraisers increase the value of a home. McKewn features Resort style zero entry pool with sun deck, a pavilion, indoor pickleball court, patio overlooking a lake and a fire pit for entertaining! All located in Dorchester II School District.
